A matrix is a 2 dimentional data object having n rows and n colums
Thats means a total of n*m elements will be there.
-----------------------------------------------------------------
If a matrix contains 2/3 elements as a zero then that matrx is known as sparse matrix.
----------------------------------------------------------------
Thats a wastage of memory and takes time to traverse tahts why we reduce the matrix in the form
row    |
col    |
value  |
------------------------------------------------------------
You can either use array of linked list to do the same
1)arrray-->arr[3][size]-->size=No of non-zero elements
2)Linked List-->
Node--> Row|COl|Value|Next-->sstructure of node
----------------------------------------------------------
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/sparse-matrix-representation/
